text_guide_automatic_academicability:
Automatically calculate the academic ability 
level based on the MoET evaluation standard.
text_guide_automatic_average:
1) Score: The semester average is automatically 
calculated based on the weighted rate 
by examination.
[weighted rate]
- Oral Examination : 1
- Fifteen Minute Examination : 1
- Fourtyfive Minute Examination : 2
- Examination at the end of the semester : 3

2) Evaluation Comment : Automatically calculate the semester average based on the examination results.
More than 2/3 of the examination results
PASS = PASS
Less than 2/3 of the examination results
FAIL = FAIL
text_guide_automatic_average2:
1) Score: The semester average is automatically calculated based on the weighted rate by semester.
[weighted rate]
- 1st Semester : 1
- 2nd Semester : 2

2) Evaluation Comment : Automatically calculate the evaluation comment based on the below standard.
Participated in both semester
1st Semester PASS, 2nd Semester PASS = PASS
1st Semester FAIL, 2nd Semester PASS = PASS
1st Semester PASS, 2nd Semester FAIL = FAIL
1st Semester FAIL, 2nd Semester FAIL = FAIL
Participated in one semester
1st or 2nd Semester PASS = PASS
1st or 2nd Semester FAIL = FAIL
text_guide_automatic_score:
- Retrieve scores from test results.
- If there are no subject tests, they will be blank.
- If you have more than one exam, the average score is displayed.

[Reflected Score by grade]
1st ~ 3th Grade : Examination at the end of the semester
4th, 5th Grade : Examination in the middle of the semester, Examination at the end of the semester
